Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile a comprehensive exploration report.

## Comprehensive DAW UI Layer Exploration

I've completed a thorough exploration of the DAW codebase's UI layer. Here's the complete findings:

### 1. FILE STRUCTURE UNDER src/ui/

**Main Directories:**
```
src/ui/
├── arrangement/          - Timeline/arrangement editor
├── controls/             - Interactive UI controls (Fader, DrumPad, etc.)
├── drum-machine/         - Drum machine panel
├── effects/              - Effects rack and effect panels
├── hooks/                - Custom React hooks
├── keyboard/             - Keyboard shortcuts & command system
├── media-pool/           - Audio file import/management
├── mixer/                - Mixer with channel strips
├── piano-roll/           - Piano roll MIDI editor
├── primitives/           - Base UI components (Button, Toggle, Select, etc.)
├── session/              - Session management (Recovery, Browser)
├── synth/                - Synthesizer editor UI
├── tokens/               - Design tokens (CSS variables)
└── transport/            - Transport controls (Play, Pause, BPM, etc.)
```

**Top-level UI files:**
- `DawShell.tsx` - Main shell component orchestrating all panels
